Dashboard Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
In the "a4GATE hostname" text field, you should find the a4GATE serial number.
Read the specific guide if you need to change it or in case it is not there.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
The "Data Sender ready" green tick shows whether the Data Sender is ready to
receive settings from a4conf.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
4
The "Data Sender Network" is connected properly when you see the green check
mark, as shown in the image and it's based on one of these three modes:
a. Data Sender is properly connected via wifi;
b. Data Sender is wired connected in "DHCP mode" and has successfully obtained
an IP address;
c. Data Sender is wired connected in "Static mode" and a static IP address is
properly set.
In the third mode (c) a green mark indicates that a cable is physically connected
and an IP address on the right network is set. This doesn't imply an effective
working network connection.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
5
The bidirectionality (Bidir.) status shows "Closed" (in red) when it's close,
otherwise, if it's open, it shows the remaining time in minutes (in green). The
maximum time that the bidirectionaly can remain open is 8 hours.
6
Click the "KepServer" button to view the status of Kepware services.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
7
"Version" shows the current version of the software installed on the a4GATE.
8
The right column of the first table shows the status (green or red) of each
Terafence service and of a4MONITOR. The status of the Terafence services is
strictly dependent on the correct functioning of a4MONITOR.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
If any services in this section is red, wait a few minutes. If the problem persist,
contact a4GATE support.
9
The "Plugins" table shows the status of each a4GATE Plugin.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
10
Click the "Fast Data" button to view the status of Fast Data services. For example:
HTTP, FTP and Matrix.
11
The "Connected Device" table shows the devices connected to the a4GATE with
their current status: a "green mark" indicates that the device is connected,
otherwise a "red mark" is displayed.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
If a yellow question mark is shown, a4GATE is not able to establish if there is an
active connection to the device.
